---
import BaseHead from "../../components/BaseHead.astro"
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro"
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro"
import BreakpointIndicator from "../../components/BreakpointIndicator.astro"
import TwoColumnSection from "../../components/TwoColumnSection.astro"
import { Image } from "astro:assets"

const pageTitle = "Future of Formula 1"
const description =
  "Discover what lies ahead for Formula 1 as we explore emerging technologies, sustainability initiatives, and the next generation of racing talent."
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title={pageTitle}
      description={description}
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <BreakpointIndicator />
    <Header />

    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-12">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          {pageTitle}
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
          Formula 1 has always been at the forefront of technological advancements, and the future
          promises to be no different. From cutting-edge aerodynamics to hybrid power units, the
          sport continues to evolve, pushing the boundaries of speed, efficiency, and performance.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Data & Analytics Section -->
    <TwoColumnSection
      title="Data and analytical revolution"
      content={`
        <p>
          The increasing use of data and analytics in Formula 1 is
          transforming the sport and opening up new possibilities for
          innovation and discovery. F1 teams are already using data to
          optimize car performance, track conditions, and race strategies, but
          with the emergence of new technologies such as artificial
          intelligence and machine learning, the potential for data-driven
          advancements in F1 is limitless.
        </p>
        <p>
          To keep up with this data-driven revolution, F1 engineers will need
          to have exceptional skills in data analysis and interpretation, and
          teams will need to invest in the latest technologies and tools. This
          focus on data will not only make F1 more competitive, but it will
          also drive breakthroughs and advancements with far-reaching impacts
          beyond the sport.
        </p>
      `}
      imageSrc="/blog-placeholder-1.jpg"
      imageAlt="F1 Data Analytics"
      background="gray"
    />

    <!-- New Innovations Section -->
    <TwoColumnSection
      title="New innovations and dynamics"
      content={`
        <p>
          The future of the sport also promises to be shaped by a more diverse
          and inclusive culture. F1 is taking steps to increase diversity and
          representation in the sport, including the launch of the We Race As
          One initiative, which aims to promote diversity and inclusion both
          on and off the track.
        </p>
        <p>
          As the sport becomes more diverse and inclusive, it will bring new
          perspectives and ideas to the engineering and design of the cars and
          the sport as a whole. This will not only make F1 more representative
          of the global community, but it will also help to attract new talent
          and create a more sustainable and innovative future for the sport.
        </p>
      `}
      imageSrc="/blog-placeholder-2.jpg"
      imageAlt="F1 Innovation and Development"
      reversed={true}
    />

    <!-- Harnessing Energy Section -->
    <section class="py-12 bg-gray-50">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 max-w-7xl mx-auto">
          <!-- Column 1: Introduction -->
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Harnessing the energy</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
              One of the emerging topics in the future of Formula 1 is sustainability. As a sport
              that relies heavily on technology and resources, F1 has been criticized in the past
              for its impact on the environment. However, in recent years, there has been a shift
              towards sustainability in F1. The sport has set ambitious targets for carbon
              reduction, and teams are investing in more environmentally friendly practices, such as
              using renewable energy and reducing waste.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
              Furthermore, F1 is exploring the use of alternative fuels, such as biofuels and
              hydrogen, in an effort to reduce the sport's carbon footprint. As the world becomes
              increasingly focused on sustainability, F1 is taking steps to ensure that it remains
              relevant and responsible in the eyes of fans and stakeholders alike.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Column 3: Stats -->
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
              <!-- Stat Card 1 -->
              <div class="bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-lg p-6">
                <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">39</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-300">Fuel blends tested by F1 with Aramco</p>
              </div>

              <!-- Stat Card 2 -->
              <div class="bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-lg p-6">
                <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">100%</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-300">F2 and F3 cars running on sustainable fuel</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
